        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 7:02PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 701 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Georgiana, or 16 miles southwest of Greenville, moving southeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
McKenzie, Dozier, Gantt, Georgiana, Heath, and Brantley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
